1************
 * B0103B   *
 ************
0B0103B
 ------
01. PURPOSE
 ----------
0   PROGRAM B0103B PRINTS A FORMATTED LISTING OF ALL OR SELECTIVE
    RECORDS WITHIN AN INDEXED SEQUENTIAL DATA SET AND ALSO PRO-
    VIDES INFORMATION FOR REORGANIZATION OF AN EXISTING ISAM
    DATA SET. A COPY FEATURE PERMITS THE CREATING OF A SEQUENTIAL
    DATA SET FROM AN ISAM FILE.
02. LIMITATIONS
 --------------
0   NONE.
03. INPUT DATA
 -------------
0   INPUT CONSISTS OF CONTROL STATEMENTS FOLLOWING THE SYSIN
    CARD AND AN ISAM DATA SET.  THE 3 KINDS OF CONTROL STATEMENTS
    ARE PRINT, INFO AND UNLOAD, WRITTEN IN A FREE FORM FORMAT.
0   THE UTILITY CONTROL STATEMENT FOR PRINTING THE INDEXED
    SEQUENTIAL DATA SET IS
              PRINT (KEY=VALUE) (,STOPAFT = N),(,KEYTYPE=(DISPLAY)
              -----                                      ---------
                                                          (PACKED)
0   1.   KEY = VALUE
0        THIS PARAMETER DEFINES THE LOCATION WITHIN THE FILE WHERE
         PRINTING IS TO BEGIN.  IF NO KEY PARAMETER IS PRESENT,
         PRINTING STARTS AT THE BEGINNING OF THE FILE.  THE LOCATION
         MAY BE DEFINED IN EITHER OF TWO WAYS.
0        A.   RECORD KEY
0             VALUE IS A VALID KEY OF A RECORD WITHIN THE FILE.
              THE REMAINDER OF THE FILE WILL BE PRINTED UNLESS
              THE OPERATION IS TERMINATED BY THE STOPAFT OPTION.
0        B.   GENERIC KEY.
0             VALUE IS A GENERIC KEY FOR A RECORD CLASS WITHIN
              THE FILE.  ALL RECORDS MATCHING THE GENERIC PORTION
              OF THE KEY WILL BE PRINTED UNLESS THE OPERATION IS
              TERMINATED USING THE STOPAFT OPTION.
0             EXAMPLE:  KEY FOR A FILE IS      CUST      PROD
                                             4 BYTES    4 BYTES
0             IN ORDER TO PRINT ALL RECORDS FOR CUST 4096, USE THE
              PARAMETER FORM    KEY = 4096****.
1************
 * B0103B   *
 ************
0        2.   STOPAFT = N
              N DEFINES THE NUMBER OF LOGICAL RECORDS TO BE PRINTED.
              IF THE PARAMETER IS NOT PRESENT, PRINTING CONTINUES
              UNTIL THE END OF FILE IS REACHED.
0        3.   KEYTYPE = (DISPLAY)
                        ---------
                         (PACKED)
              PACKED INDICATES THAT A KEY VALUE USED IN THE KEY
              PARAMETER APPEARS IN THE FILE IN PACKED (COMPUTATIONAL -
              3) FORMAT.  IF NO KEYTYPE IS PRESENT, DISPLAY FORMAT IS
              ASSUMED.  IF NO KEY PARAMETER IS PRESENT, KEYTYPE IS
              IGNORED.
0   THE UTILITY CONTROL STATEMENT FOR DETERMINING WHETHER A REQUIREMENT
    FOR FILE REORGANIZATION EXISTS IS
0             INFO
              ----
0             THE INFORMATION PROVIDED WILL INCLUDE:
0             1. NUMBER OF CYLINDER OVERFLOW AREAS WHICH ARE FULL.
0             2. NUMBER OF TRACKS REMAINING IN THE INDEPENDENT
                 OVERFLOW AREA.
0             3. NUMBER OF RECORDS IN PRIME DATA AREA.
0             4. NUMBER OF RECORDS IN OVERFLOW AREAS.
0   THE UTILITY CONTROL STATEMENT FOR CREATING A SEQUENTIAL DATA SET
    FROM AN EXISTING INDEXED SEQUENTIAL DATA SET IS
0             UNLOAD
              ------
04. OUTPUT DATA
 --------------
0             OPTIONS USED:
0             1. PRINT            PROVIDES A LISTING OF AN ISAM FILE ON SYSOUT.
0             2. INFO             PROVIDES INFORMATION FOR REORGANIZATION OF
                                  ISAM FILE ON SYSOUT
0             3. UNLOAD           PROVIDES A SEQUENTIAL COPY OF AN ISAM FILE
                                  FROM SYSUT1.  THE SEQUENTIAL DATA SET IS
                                  CREATED ON SYSUT2.
1************
 * B0103B   *
 ************
05. OPERATION
 ------------
0   B0103B HAS BEEN CATALOGUED AND PLACED IN THE OS/360 LIBRARY.
    THE FOLLOWING CONTROL CARDS ARE REQUIRED TO CAUSE LOADING
    AND EXECUTION OF THE PROGRAM.
0   //          JOB
0   //JOBLIB     DD     DSNAME=MISDLIB,DISP=(OLD,PASS)
0   //STEP01    EXEC    PGM=B0103B
0   //SYSUT1     DD     (PARAMETERS DEFINING INPUT DATA SET)
0   //SYSUT2     DD     (PARAMETERS DEFINING OUTPUT DATA SET)
0   //SYSOUT     DD     SYSOUT=A,DCB=(,LRECL=120,BLKSIZE=120)
0   //SYSPRINT   DD     SYSOUT=A
0   //SYSIN      DD     *
              UTILITY CONTROL STATEMENT
0   /*
0   AN INDEXED SEQUENTIAL DATA SET SHOULD HAVE THE FOLLOWING
    DCB PARAMETERS:
                   RECFM
                   LRECL
                   BLKSIZE
                   DSORG = IS.
                   ----------
0   A SEQUENTIAL DATA SET SHOULD HAVE THE FOLLOWING DCB PARAMETERS:
                   RECFM
                   BLKSIZE
                   LRECL  (IT MUST BE 1 LESS THAN THE ISAM
                           LOGICAL RECORD LENGTH.)
1************
 * B0103B   *
 ************
06. EXAMPLES
 -----------
0   1.  JOB GIVES FILE RECORD DISTRIBUTION STATISTICS.
0   //INFO        JOB
0   //JOBLIB       DD   DSNAME=MISDLIB,DISP=(OLD,PASS)
0   //STEP1      EXEC   PGM B0103B
0   //SYSOUT       DD   SYSOUT=A
0   //SYSPRINT     DD   SYSOUT=A
0   //SYSUT1       DD   DSNAME=ISAMFILE,UNIT=193
0   //                  VOLUME=SER=DSK003,
0   //                  DCB=(,DSORG=IS),DISP=(OLD,KEEP)
0   //SYSIN        DD   *
0     INFO
0   /*
0   2.  JOB PRINTS 30 RECORDS OF THE DATA SET BEGINNING WITH
        THE GENERIC KEY 4096****.
0   //PRINT       JOB
0   //JOBLIB       DD   DSNAME=MISDLIB,DISP=OLD
0   //STEP2      EXEC   PGM=B0103B
0   //SYSOUT       DD   SYSOUT=A
0   //SYSPRINT     DD   SYSOUT=A
0   //SYSUT1       DD   DSNAME=ISAMFILE,UNIT=2311,
0   //                  DCB=(,DSORG=IS),DISP=OLD
0   //SYSIN        DD   *
0     PRINT       KEY=4096****,STOPAFT=30
0   /*
0   3.  JOB WILL READ ISAM FILE IN SCAN MODE AND CREATE A
        SEQUENTIAL FILE.
0   //UNLOAD      JOB
0   //JOBLIB       DD   DSNAME=MISDLIB,DISP=OLD
0   //STEP3      EXEC   PGM=B0103B
0   //SYSOUT       DD   SYSOUT=A
0   //SYSPRINT     DD   SYSOUT=A
0   //SYSUT1       DD   DSNAME=ISAMFILE,UNIT=2311,DISP=OLD,
0   //                  DCB=(,DSORG=IS,LRECL=161,BLKSIZE=3542)
0   //SYSUT2       DD   DSNAME=SEQUENTIAL,UNIT=TAPE9,DISP=(,PASS),
0   //                  DCB=(,LRECL=160,BLKSIZE=1600,RECFM=FB)
0   //SYSIN        DD   *
         UNLOAD
0   /*
